The Asiatic gambler is desperate . 
The Malayan , however , does not always tamely submit to this last stroke of fortune . 
Indeed , they play night and day until they have lost all they are worth , and then they usually go and hang themselves . 
If we turn our course northward , and penetrate the regions of ice perpetual , we find that the driven snow cannot effectually quench the flames of gambling . 
They glow amid the regions of the frozen pole . 
If we descend thence into the Western hemisphere , we find that the passion for gambling forms a distinguishing feature in the character of all the rude natives of the American continent . 
, their apparel , and at length their personal liberty , on games of chance . 
There is one thing , however , which must be recorded to their credit and to our shame . 
When they have lost their all , they do not follow the example of our refined gamesters . 
They neither murmur nor repine . 
Not a fretful word escapes them . 
They bear the frowns of fortune with a philosophic composure . 
There is no doubt , then , that this propensity is part and parcel of the unsophisticated savage . 
Take the grand prototypes of Britons , the Romans of old . 
That gamesters they were ! And how gambling recruited the ranks of the desperadoes who gave them insurrectionary trouble ! Catiline's army of scoundrels , for instance . 
Horace , Juvenal , Persius , Cicero , and other writers , attest the fact of Roman gambling most eloquently , most indignantly . 
