So the Pandavas made haste with their wife Draupadi , and departed out of the city of Hastinapur . 
So they sat down again to play , and Sakuni had a set of cheating dice as before , and with them he won the game . 
When Duhsasana saw that Sakuni had won the game , he danced about for joy and he cried out Now is established the Raj of Duryodhana . 
But Bhima said , Be not elated with joy , but remember my words The day will come when I will drink your blood , or I am not the son of Kunti . 
Such was the great gambling match at Hastinapur in the heroic age of India . 
