High play was always the etiquette at court , but the sittings became less frequent and were abridged . 
The king , says Madame de Sevigne , has not given over playing , but the sittings are not so long . 
At the death of Louis XIV . 
three fourths of the nation thought of nothing but gambling . 
The nation seemed all mad with the excitement of play . 
