There was also a great deal of play at Graham's , the Union , the Cocoa Tree , and other clubs of the second order in point of fashion . 
Here large sums were hazarded with equal rashness , and remarkable characters started up . 
Among the most conspicuous was the late Colonel Aubrey , who literally passed his life at play . 
He did nothing else , morning , noon , and night and it was computed that he had paid more than sixty thousand pounds for card money . 
He was a very fine player at all games , and a shrewd , clever man . 
He had been twice to India and made two fortunes . 
It was said that he lost the first on his way home , transferred himself from one ship to another without landing , went back , and made the second . 
