That was indeed the forest of all evils , but an evil to which every deep gamestress was inevitably exposed . 
Hogarth strikingly illustrated this phase of womanhood in England , in his small picture painted for the Earl of Charlemont , and entitled Picquet , or Virtue in Danger . 
It shows a young lady , who , during a tete a tete , had just lost all her money to a handsome officer of her own age . 
He is represented in the act of returning her a handful of bank bills , with the hope of exchanging them for another acquisition and more delicate plunder . 
