The French borrowed the idea from the Italians . 
From the year the state derived a revenue from the lotteries , although from to the French parliament repeatedly endeavoured to suppress them as social evils . 
At the marriage of Louis XIV . 
a lottery was organized to distribute the royal presents to the people after the fashion of the Roman emperor . 
Lotteries were multiplied during this reign and that of Louis XV . 
In the Royal Lottery of France was established . 
This was abolished in , re established at the commencement of the Republic but finally all lotteries were prohibited by law in , excepting for benevolent purposes . 
One of the most remarkable of these lotteries for benevolent purposes' was the Lottery of the Gold Lingots , authorized in , to favour emigration to California . 
In this lottery the grand prize was a lingot of gold valued at about L . 
The old French lottery consisted of numbers , that is , from No. to No. , and the drawing was five numbers at a time . 
Five wheels were established at Paris , Lyons , Strasbourg , Bordeaus , and Lille . 
A drawing took place every ten days at each city . 
The first English lottery mentioned in history was drawn in the year . 
It consisted of , lots , at s . 
The prizes were plate and the profits were to go towards repairing the havens or ports of this kingdom . 
It was drawn at the west door of St Paul's Cathedral . 
The drawing began on the th of January , , and continued incessantly , DAY AND NIGHT , till the th of May following . 
Another lottery was held at the same place in , King James having permitted it in favour of the plantation of English colonies in Virginia . 
One Thomas Sharplys , a tailor of London , won the chief prize , which was crowns in fair plate . 
The printed scheme of this lottery is still in the possession of the Antiquarian Society of London . 
In , a lottery was granted to supply London with water . 
The tickets were all disposed of in less than six months , friends and enemies joining in the speculation . 
The first parliamentary lottery was instituted in , and from this period till the passing of a lottery bill was in the programme of every session . 
Up to the close of the th century the prizes were generally paid in the form of terminable , and sometimes of perpetual , annuities . 
Loans were also raised by granting a bonus of lottery tickets to all who subscribed a certain amount . 
The last public lottery in Great Britain was drawn in October , . 
The lotteries exerted a most baneful influence on trade , by relaxing the sinews of industry and fostering the destructive spirit of gaming among all orders of men . 
